       Layout 
    #going-responsive.stripe
      .contain
        h3 Going Responsive
        p
          | Webplate includes its custom built
          a(href='http://getwebplate.com/plugins/blueplate') Blueplate
          | layout engine and can be used in one of two ways. You can either build your layouts using the classing implementation or you can build it using the recommended mixin implementation (requires SASS). See a basic example of both below.
        p  
        h4 Classed Implementation
        p HTML
        pre.prettyprint.linenums.showcase-code.
          \n<div class="class-example row">
              <div class="span-12 span-large-2">Left</div>
              <div class="span-6 span-large-8">Middle</div>
              <div class="span-6 span-large-2">Right</div>
          </div>
                    
        p
          | RESULT (Screen Width:
          span.screen-width
          | px)
        .class-example.row
          .span-12.span-large-2 Left
          .span-6.span-large-8 Middle
          .span-6.span-large-2 Right
        p  
        h4 Mixin Implementation
        p HTML
        pre.prettyprint.linenums.showcase-code.
          \n<div class="atomic-example">
              <div class="left-col">Left</div>
              <div class="middle-col">Middle</div>
              <div class="right-col">Right</div>
          </div>
                    
        p SASS
        pre.prettyprint.linenums.showcase-code.
          \n.atomic-example {
              @include row();
          
              // Columns - mobile first
              .left-col, .right-col, .middle-col {
                  @include span(12);
              }
          
              // Over 700px
              @include respond-to(large) {
                  .left-col {
                      @include span-new(6);
                  }
                  .middle-col, .right-col {
                      @include span-new(3);
                  }
              }
          
              // Over 800px
              @include respond-to(50em) {
                  .left-col {
                      @include span-new(12);
                  }
                  .middle-col {
                      @include span-new(9);
                  }
                  .right-col {
                      @include span-new(3);
                  }
              }
          
              // Over 900px
              @include respond-to(56.250em) {
                  .left-col, .right-col {
                      @include span-new(2);
                  }
                  .middle-col {
                      @include span-new(8);
                  }
              }
          }
                    
        p
          | RESULT (Screen Width:
          span.screen-width
          | px)
        .atomic-example
          .left-col Left
          .middle-col Middle
          .right-col Right
        p  
        p
          | There is a lot more that can be done and configured and it is recommended that you read the online documentation on layouts.
          p
            a.btn-primary(href='http://getwebplate.com/documentation/layout') Read Documentation
